 ignored. The quality and\n  completeness of evidence determines whether the decision can be\n  considered informed.", :support-status nil} #:concept{:assumptions ["Legitimacy is a composite concept derived from the other five consensus dimensions." "Strong scores on all five dimensions imply legitimacy." "Concept labels do not change protocol validity."], :evidence nil, :id :consensus/legitimacy, :known-gaps nil, :mappings #:concept{:actions {:accept-outcome {:description "Consent to the outcome despite disagreement.", :maps-to [:protocol.action/accept-split :protocol.action/waive-appeal], :mapping/status :native}, :assess-legitimacy {:description "Evaluate the strength of legitimacy signals.", :maps-to [:protocol.action/verify :protocol.action/audit], :mapping/status :native}, :challenge-legitimacy {:description "Argue that authority, evidence, process, or timeliness was flawed.", :maps-to [:protocol.action/dispute :protocol.action/appeal :protocol.action/challenge-resolution], :mapping/status :native}, :establish-legitimacy {:description "Produce evidence, follow procedure, and issue a timely ruling that strengthens acceptance.", :maps-to [:protocol.action/resolve :protocol.action/settle :protocol.action/submit-evidence], :mapping/status :native}}, :entities {:illegitimacy-signal {:description "Evidence or marker suggesting the outcome is not legitimate.", :maps-to [:protocol.entity/dispute :protocol.entity/appeal], :mapping/status :native}, :legitimacy-signal {:description "Evidence or marker suggesting the outcome is legitimate.", :maps-to [:protocol.entity/settlement :protocol.entity/evidence], :mapping/status :native}}, :outcomes {:legitimacy-contested {:description "Legitimacy was formally challenged and a decision is pending.", :maps-to [:protocol.outcome/appealed], :mapping/status :native}, :legitimacy-failed {:description "Multiple dimensions compromised; outcome is unlikely to be accepted.", :maps-to [:protocol.outcome/stuck :protocol.outcome/disputed], :mapping/confidence :approximate, :mapping/note "Legitimacy failure may leave funds stuck or the outcome actively disputed", :mapping/status :approximate}, :legitimacy-strong {:description "All dimensions (authority, evidence, finality, escalation, liveness) are satisfactory.", :maps-to [:protocol.outcome/resolved], :mapping/status :native}, :legitimacy-weak {:description "At least one dimension was compromised but outcome was still reached.", :maps-to [:protocol.outcome/adversarial-resolution], :mapping/status :native}}, :roles {:legitimacy-assessor {:description "Party evaluating whether the outcome is legitimate.", :maps-to [:protocol.actor/verifier], :mapping/status :native}, :legitimacy-challenger {:description "Party rejecting the outcome as illegitimate.", :maps-to [:protocol.actor/sender :protocol.actor/recipient], :mapping/status :native}, :legitimacy-claimer {:description "Party asserting that the outcome should be accepted.", :maps-to [:protocol.actor/resolver :protocol.actor/governance], :mapping/status :native}}}, :maturity nil, :name "Consensus legitimacy", :not-claimed ["This stakeholder-facing concept does not assert implementation, deployment, legal, economic-safety, or benchmark coverage." "Protocol support must be established independently through adapter capabilities, executable scenarios, benchmark claims, and deployment configuration."], :out-of-scope ["Real-world political or social legitimacy." "Normative or ethical judgments about the outcome." "Acceptance by parties who always reject any adverse outcome."], :stakeholder-question "Should I accept this outcome as binding, or are there grounds —\n  procedural, evidentiary, or authority-based — to challenge it?", :summary "Why should parties accept the outcome as binding? Legitimacy derives\n  from proper authority, fair process, adequate evidence, timely\n  resolution, and available escalation. Weak or failed legitimacy means\n  one or more of these dimensions was compromised.", :support-status nil} #:concept{:assumptions ["Confidence is distinct from pass/fail. A claim can pass with low confidence if coverage is thin. A claim can fail with high confidence if the failure is deterministic and well evidenced." "Confidence is dimensional, not scalar. Evidence confidence, coverage confidence, determinism confidence, and attestation confidence should be reported separately before any aggregate label is derived."], :evidence nil, :id :concept/confidence, :known-gaps nil, :mappings #:concept{:actions #:action{:attest-result {:description "Produce an attestation for a claim result, linking evidence artifacts into a chain.", :maps-to [:protocol.action/attest], :mapping/status :native}, :evaluate-claim {:description "Assess a claim result against expectations and theory, producing a pass/fail verdict.", :maps-to [:protocol.action/evaluate-claim], :mapping/status :native}, :test-scenario {:description "Execute a scenario to produce a result for one or more claims.", :maps-to [:protocol.action/run-scenario], :mapping/status :native}}, :entities #:entity{:benchmark-run {:description "A full execution of a benchmark pack producing a set of claim results with associated confidence values.", :maps-to [:protocol.entity/benchmark-run], :mapping/status :native}, :claim-result {:description "A structured outcome for a single claim tested by a scenario or benchmark.", :maps-to [:protocol.entity/claim-result], :mapping/status :native}, :evidence-artifact {:description "A hash-addressed artifact that supports a claim result (replay output, attestation, registry node).", :maps-to [:protocol.entity/evidence], :mapping/status :native}}, :outcomes #:outcome{:high-confidence {:description "The claim result is supported by strong evidence, broad coverage, deterministic replay, and independent attestation.", :maps-to [:protocol.outcome/pass], :mapping/status :native}, :low-confidence {:description "The claim result has significant evidence, coverage, or determinism gaps and should not be relied upon without further investigation.", :maps-to [:protocol.outcome/warn], :mapping/status :native}, :medium-confidence {:description "The claim result is supported but has gaps in coverage, non-deterministic elements, or missing attestation.", :maps-to [:protocol.outcome/warn], :mapping/status :native}}, :roles #:role{:protocol-designer {:description "Uses confidence to assess whether invariant and benchmark results are trustworthy enough to inform protocol changes.", :maps-to [], :mapping/status :not-modelled}, :researcher {:description "Uses confidence dimensions to qualify benchmark findings and identify gaps.", :maps-to [], :mapping/status :not-modelled}, :reviewer {:description "Evaluates whether benchmark results have adequate evidence, coverage, and determinism to support their claims.", :maps-to [], :mapping/status :not-modelled}}}, :maturity nil, :name "Confidence", :not-claimed ["This stakeholder-facing concept does not assert implementation, deployment, legal, economic-safety, or benchmark coverage." "Protocol support must be established independently through adapter capabilities, executable scenarios, benchmark claims, and deployment configuration."], :out-of-scope ["This concept does not define a minimum confidence threshold for protocol acceptance." "This concept does not assign trust scores to individual actors or oracles." "This concept does not address statistical or Bayesian confidence intervals."], :stakeholder-question "How strongly is this result supported?", :summary "The strength of support for a result or claim, distinct from pass/fail status.", :support-status nil} #:concept{:assumptions ["A result is valid only under the configuration that produced it. Claims of general protocol safety must be qualified by the configuration space explored." "Configuration includes protocol parameters, module selections, benchmark definitions, execution options, and temporal assumptions." "Configuration should be explicitly hashed and recorded in the artifact registry for every run that produces a claim result."], :evidence nil, :id :concept/configuration, :known-gaps nil, :mappings #:concept{:actions #:action{:detect-drift {:description "Compare two configuration hashes to determine whether settings have changed between runs.", :maps-to [:protocol.action/compare-configurations], :mapping/status :native}, :hash-configuration {:description "Compute a canonical hash of the active configuration for reproducibility linking.", :maps-to [:protocol.action/hash-configuration], :mapping/status :native}, :parameterise {:description "Assign a configuration value to a protocol parameter, module selection, or execution option.", :maps-to [:protocol.action/parameterise], :mapping/status :native}}, :entities #:entity{:benchmark-pack {:description "A named collection of scenarios, scoring rules, claim sets, and configuration references.", :maps-to [:protocol.entity/benchmark-pack], :mapping/status :native}, :execution-replay {:description "A deterministic replay run linked to a specific configuration hash.", :maps-to [:protocol.entity/replay], :mapping/status :native}, :scenario-definition {:description "A complete scenario map including events, agents, protocol-params, and expectations.", :maps-to [:protocol.entity/scenario], :mapping/status :native}}, :outcomes #:outcome{:configuration-drift {:description "Two related runs were executed under different configurations that were assumed to be identical.", :maps-to [:protocol.outcome/fail], :mapping/status :native}, :configuration-gap {:description "Some configuration parameters are implicit, unrecorded, or inferred rather than explicit.", :maps-to [:protocol.outcome/fail], :mapping/status :native}, :configuration-known {:description "The full configuration is recorded, hashed, and available in the artifact registry.", :maps-to [:protocol.outcome/pass], :mapping/status :native}}, :roles #:role{:protocol-designer {:description "Uses configuration to define the conditions under which protocol properties are expected to hold.", :maps-to [], :mapping/status :not-modelled}, :researcher {:description "Compares results across configurations to understand how parameter choices affect protocol behaviour.", :maps-to [], :mapping/status :not-modelled}, :reviewer {:description "Needs to know the exact configuration under which a result was produced to assess reproducibility and applicability.", :maps-to [], :mapping/status :not-modelled}}}, :maturity nil, :name "Configuration", :not-claimed ["This stakeholder-facing concept does not assert implementation, deployment, legal, economic-safety, or benchmark coverage." "Protocol support must be established independently through adapter capabilities, executable scenarios, benchmark claims, and deployment configuration."], :out-of-scope ["This concept does not prescribe which configuration parameters should be varied in a sensitivity analysis." "This concept does not define a canonical configuration for production deployment." "This concept does not address environmental configuration outside the protocol and execution layers (e.g., hardware, OS, network)."], :stakeholder-question "Under what conditions does this result hold?", :summary "The explicit settings under which a scenario, benchmark, or claim result is valid.", :support-status nil} #:concept{:assumptions [], :failure-modes [:failure/unmodelled-sink :failure/unmodelled-source :failure/double-counted-liability :failure/false-conservation-failure :failure/rounding-dust-unaccounted :failure/wrong-claimant-allocation :failure/hidden-shortfall :failure/stale-claimable-after-cancel], :id :robustness/protocol-value-conservation, :maps-to {:benchmark-domain :domain/protocol-value-conservation, :claims [:claim/funds-conserved :claim/slashing-conservation :claim/no-leakage-beyond-shortfall :claim/partial-fill-fairness :claim/yield-preserved-during-shortfall :claim/appeal-bond-adequacy :claim/no-over-slashing :claim/solvency-status], :evidence [:evidence/world-before :evidence/world-after :evidence/state-diff :evidence/claimable-classification :evidence/allocation-result :evidence/invariant-result :evidence/trace], :framework-concepts [:concept/conservation], :scenarios ["settlement release/refund scenarios" "yield shortfall scenarios" "partial-fill withdrawal scenarios" "resolver slashing scenarios" "appeal and bond custody scenarios" "cancellation/finality scenarios"]}, :name "Protocol value conservation and allocation", :out-of-scope [], :stakeholder-language "When value moves through the protocol, every unit should be explainable:\n    paid out, refunded, held, slashed, assigned as a fee, recorded as a\n    shortfall, deferred as a recognised claim, waived by rule, or tracked as\n    bounded residual dust. The benchmark should make it clear where value\n    went and whether the distribution followed the intended rule.", :stakeholder-question "When value moves through the protocol, every unit should be explainable:\n    paid out, refunded, held, slashed, assigned as a fee, recorded as a\n    shortfall, deferred as a recognised claim, waived by rule, or tracked as\n    bounded residual dust. The benchmark should make it clear where value\n    went and whether the distribution followed the intended rule.", :summary "Whether protocol value is fully accounted for, correctly classified,\n    and distributed according to explicit protocol rules across settlement,\n    yield, bonds, slashing, fees, shortfalls, deferred claims, residuals,\n    and cancellation paths.", :title "Protocol value conservation and allocation", :why-it-matters "Most serious protocol failures are value-accounting failures: value can\n    disappear, appear without a source, be counted twice, be assigned to the\n    wrong bucket, or be hidden as an implicit shortfall. This benchmark\n    dimension gives reviewers a direct way to inspect whether Sew's\n    value-moving mechanisms remain auditable under ordinary, adversarial,\n    and shortfall conditions."}]}, :evidence/hash "c8d9fc38ba018e523834cf79bf1b444e0e7a1745ea193c31765f6f88cd6598f0", :run/manifest {:adapter "class resolver_sim.benchmark.runner.SewAdapter", :declared-run-count 1, :execution-count 15, :metrics {:declared-run-count 1, :execution-count 15, :passed 15, :passed-execution-count 15, :total 15, :unique-scenario-count 15}, :scenario-count 15, :scenario-hashes [{:file "/home/user/Code/.workspaces/agent-c/scenarios/edn/S78_yield-aave-partial-liquidity-release.edn", :outcome :pass, :benchmark/run-count 1, :benchmark/run-index 1, :scenario/evidence-root "4cb790b99bbb34141f9d4ffc77e9548267ac7284594544667472b37b52d7e3cc", :scenario/id nil} {:file "/home/user/Code/.workspaces/agent-c/scenarios/edn/S78_yield-negative-yield-release-path.edn", :outcome :pass, :benchmark/run-count 1, :benchmark/run-index 1, :scenario/evidence-root "84c1e28a8a26cb1b53f30924da8a1ab43e05527bda8e5b5adaef083b66012abb", :scenario/id nil} {:file "/home/user/Code/.workspaces/agent-c/scenarios/edn/S79_yield-aave-partial-liquidity-dispute-resolution.edn", :outcome :pass, :benchmark/run-count 1, :benchmark/run-index 1, :scenario/evidence-root "b1367922fa2d2818e12bd6bfd68f1c1b6ba6d751efcb3be5c7b09b7456a53b88", :scenario/id nil} {:file "/home/user/Code/.workspaces/agent-c/scenarios/edn/S79_yield-negative-yield-dispute-refund-path.edn", :outcome :pass, :benchmark/run-count 1, :benchmark/run-index 1, :scenario/evidence-root "7450c5110acba0bdc9e59befed32293abf4b31733bee250ad9cb787c8dd18296", :scenario/id nil} {:file "/home/user/Code/.workspaces/agent-c/scenarios/edn/S80_yield-mostly-liquid-partial-liquidity.edn", :outcome :pass, :benchmark/run-count 1, :benchmark/run-index 1, :scenario/evidence-root "4cb790b99bbb34141f9d4ffc77e9548267ac7284594544667472b37b52d7e3cc", :scenario/id nil} {:file "/home/user/Code/.workspaces/agent-c/scenarios/edn/S80_yield-aave-partial-liquidity-governance-disable-post-create.edn", :outcome :pass, :benchmark/run-count 1, :benchmark/run-index 1, :scenario/eviden